    "body": "``` bash\n./geth --datadir /tmp/unlock.test --password <(echo -n '1234') account new\n# Address: {0xd8e608ae9f160dd54253ca26e5295dc1dbf75982}\n./geth --datadir /tmp/unlock.test --password <(echo -n '1234') --unlock primary js <(echo \"console.log(eth.getBalance(eth.accounts[0]));\") 2> /tmp/unlock.test.log\n# Account '0xd8e608ae9f160dd54253ca26e5295dc1dbf75982' unlocked.\n# 0\n```\n\ni have a suspicion. you know `echo` puts a new line at the end of its output. So if your password is '1234' that won't match \"1234\\n\". So you need to use `<(echo -n 1234)`. Check maybe your plaintext file had a trailing newline too. Implementation is trivial and always worked. :)\n",
